---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="Compound Interest: How Your Money Grows Over Time" description="Understand compound interest with clear examples and the formula. See how small amounts grow into large sums and why starting early matters so much." keywords="compound interest, compound interest formula, how interest works, money growth, savings interest, investment returns, compound interest calculator">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Finance</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Compound Interest: How Your Money Grows Over Time</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 9, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Albert Einstein reportedly called compound interest "the eighth wonder of the world." Whether or not the quote is real, the principle is powerful: earning interest on your interest can turn small savings into significant wealth over time.</p>

      <h2>Simple vs Compound Interest</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Simple interest:</strong> You earn interest only on your original deposit. $1,000 at 5% earns $50 every year forever</li>
        <li><strong>Compound interest:</strong> You earn interest on your deposit PLUS previous interest. $1,000 at 5% earns $50 in year 1, then $52.50 in year 2, then $55.13 in year 3, and so on</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The Formula</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">A = final amount | P = principal | r = annual rate | n = compounds per year | t = years</p>
      </div>

      <h2>The Power of Time: A Real Example</h2>
      <p>Invest $5,000 at 7% annual return (compounded annually):</p>
      <ul>
        <li>After 10 years: $9,836 (almost doubled)</li>
        <li>After 20 years: $19,348 (nearly 4x)</li>
        <li>After 30 years: $38,061 (over 7.5x)</li>
        <li>After 40 years: $74,872 (nearly 15x your original investment)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The Rule of 72</h2>
      <p>Want to know how long it takes to double your money? Divide 72 by your interest rate:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>At 4%: 72 / 4 = 18 years to double</li>
        <li>At 6%: 72 / 6 = 12 years to double</li>
        <li>At 8%: 72 / 8 = 9 years to double</li>
        <li>At 10%: 72 / 10 = 7.2 years to double</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Starting Early Matters</h2>
      <p>Consider two investors both earning 7% annually:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Person A:</strong> Invests $200/month from age 25 to 65 (40 years) = $96,000 invested, grows to approximately $525,000</li>
        <li><strong>Person B:</strong> Invests $200/month from age 35 to 65 (30 years) = $72,000 invested, grows to approximately $243,000</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Person A invested only $24,000 more but ended up with $282,000 more. That is the power of those extra 10 years of compounding.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/tools/loan" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Loan Calculator →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/tools/loan" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Tool →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
